      "opening_notes": "Evans Gambit (C51): After accepting with 4...Bxb4, the correct retreat on move 5 is Ba5 not Bc5. Ba5 is stable — out of the way of d4 — and does not need to move again. Bc5 gets hit by d4 and forces a second retreat (Bd6 or similar), wasting two tempos on the same piece. General rule: accept the gambit pawn but then develop other pieces rather than keep moving the same bishop."
